    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a pristine FD3S Mazda RX-7, representing the pinnacle of rotary performance. This example features the original 13B-REW engine with its sequential twin-turbocharger system functioning exactly to factory specifications, providing a seamless transition between the primary and secondary boost phases. Recent compression tests yield high, consistent results across all rotor faces, indicating excellent apex seal integrity. The vehicle retains its lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and front-midship layout, preserving the legendary 50/50 weight distribution. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. This unmolested chassis shows no signs of heat-cycle fatigue or vacuum system degradation, making it a mechanically superior specimen for the discerning enthusiast.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
